<h2 id=3D"what-is-discriminant">What is Discriminant Algebra?</h2>
<p>When solving with the quadratic formula the =E2=80=9Cdiscriminant=E2=80=
=9D is the value that helps us figure out the types of solution. It is a sp=
ecial functions of the co-efficient of an equation (quadratic equation) who=
se value reveals information about the roots of the equation.</p>
<p>The discriminant is calculated by squaring the =E2=80=9Cb=E2=80=9D term =
and subtraction 4-times the =E2=80=9Ca=E2=80=9D term times the =E2=80=9Cc=
=E2=80=9D term. Discriminant is also represented by =CE=94 (delta) beside =
