es a positive and negative discriminant represent?</h2>
<p>A positive discriminant denotes that the quadratic has two different rea=
l numbers solutions. A discriminant of zero denotes that the quadratic cons=
ist of a repeated real number solution. A negative discriminant denotes tha=
t neither of the solution is real number.</p>
